  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine effectiveness of parents' manipulation in newborn
      with talipes calcaneovalgus over observation group.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Talipes calcaneovalgus is one of the common foot deformity in newborn. Most of patients can
      be cure without specific treatment. Manipulation was easy method that parents can preform by
      their own and may be beneficial in speeding resolution of deformity.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
